INSERT INTO `chat_history` VALUES (1,NULL,'What are the top engineering colleges?','I can help you with college information! Please check our college listings or use the rank predictor to find colleges matching your CET rank. For specific details, you can browse our database or ask me more specific questions.','2025-11-20 20:20:01'),(2,NULL,'what about srinivas','I\'m here to help with your college admission queries! I can assist with college information, course details, admission deadlines, fee structures, and rank-based predictions. Please ask me a specific question, and I\'ll do my best to help you.','2025-11-20 20:20:19'),(3,NULL,'What is the eligibility for B.Tech?','I\'m here to help with your college admission queries! I can assist with college information, course details, admission deadlines, fee structures, and rank-based predictions. Please ask me a specific question, and I\'ll do my best to help you.','2025-11-20 20:20:35'),(4,NULL,'How do I apply for scholarships?','I\'m here to help with your college admission queries! I can assist with college information, course details, admission deadlines, fee structures, and rank-based predictions. Please ask me a specific question, and I\'ll do my best to help you.','2025-11-20 20:21:59'),(9,1,'What are the top engineering colleges?','I can help you with college information! Please check our college listings or use the rank predictor to find colleges matching your CET rank. For specific details, you can browse our database or ask me more specific questions.','2025-11-20 20:45:58'),(10,NULL,'Tell me about admission deadlines','Admission deadlines vary by college and exam. Please check our exam schedules section or specify which college/exam you\'re asking about for accurate deadline information.','2025-11-20 20:46:42'),(11,NULL,'cet','I\'m here to help with your college admission queries! I can assist with college information, course details, admission deadlines, fee structures, and rank-based predictions. Please ask me a specific question, and I\'ll do my best to help you.','2025-11-20 20:46:53'),(12,NULL,'What are the top engineering colleges?','I can help you with college information! Please check our college listings or use the rank predictor to find colleges matching your CET rank. For specific details, you can browse our database or ask me more specific questions.','2025-11-20 20:52:16'),(13,NULL,'hi','Namaste! \n\nWelcome to Admit Genie, your friendly AI assistant for Indian college admissions. I\'m here to help you navigate the college admission process.\n\nTo get started, could you please tell me what you\'re looking for? Are you a student looking for information on colleges, courses, or admission processes? Or perhaps you\'re a parent seeking guidance on the best colleges for your child?\n\nType \'college info\', \'course details\', \'admission process\', or any other relevant query to get started. If I don\'t have the specific information you\'re looking for, I\'ll do my best to guide you on where to find it.','2025-11-21 01:50:05'),(14,NULL,'college info','You\'re interested in learning more about top Indian colleges. I\'ve got some exciting information for you!\n\nOur database includes information on the top 5 Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs). Here\'s a brief overview:\n\n1. **Indian Institute of Technology Bombay** (Ranking: 1)\n   - Location: Powai, Mumbai\n   - Known for its strong programs in engineering, management, and science.\n\n2. **Indian Institute of Technology Delhi** (Ranking: 2)\n   - Location: Hauz Khas, New Delhi\n   - Renowned for its research-oriented programs in engineering, computer science, and management.\n\n3. **Indian Institute of Technology Madras** (Ranking: 3)\n   - Location: Sardar Patel Road, Chennai\n   - Strong programs in engineering, computer science, and humanities.\n\n4. **Indian Institute of Technology Kanpur** (Ranking: 4)\n   - Location: Kanpur\n   - Focus on engineering, computer science, and basic sciences.\n\n5. **Indian Institute of Technology Kharagpur** (Ranking: 5)\n   - Location: Kharagpur\n   - Known for its programs in engineering, computer science, and humanities.\n\nIf you\'d like more specific information about these colleges or any other details, feel free to ask!','2025-11-21 01:50:17'),(15,NULL,'what about in karnatka','Hello! I\'d be happy to help you with college admissions in Karnataka.\n\nKarnataka has a well-developed education system with numerous top-ranked colleges and universities. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. **Engineering colleges:**\n   - National Institute of Technology (NITK) Surathkal\n   - Indian Institute of Technology (IIT) Dharwad\n   - Visvesvaraya Technological University (VTU) colleges in Bengaluru, Mysuru, and other locations\n2. **Medical colleges:**\n   - Kasturba Medical College (KMC) Mangaluru\n   - Bangalore Medical College and Research Institute (BMCRI)\n   - SDM College of Medical Sciences\n3. **Law colleges:**\n   - National Law School of India University (NLSIU) Bengaluru\n   - Bengaluru Institute of Legal Studies\n   - Symbiosis Law School Bengaluru\n4. **Business schools:**\n   - Indian Institute of Management (IIM) Bengaluru\n   - Xavier Labour Relations Institute (XLRI) Bengaluru\n   - Institute of Management Studies (IMS) Bengaluru\n\nFor CET rank-based college predictions, I can provide you with general guidelines. Based on the Common Entrance Test (CET) scores, here\'s a rough estimate of the colleges you might get into:\n\n- 80,000+ CET rank: VTU colleges, private engineering colleges\n- 40,000-80,000 CET rank: Reputed private engineering colleges, some government colleges\n- 20,000-40,000 CET rank: Top-tier engineering colleges, some medical colleges\n- Below 20,000 CET rank: IITs, NITs, top-ranked government colleges, some medical colleges\n\nPlease note that these are general predictions based on past trends and may vary depending on various factors like CET scores, other entrance exams, and college-specific cut-offs.\n\nFor more information on college fees, admission processes, and scholarship opportunities, I recommend visiting the respective college websites or contacting them directly. You can also check with the Karnataka Examination Authority (KEA) for CET-related information.\n\nIf you have any specific questions or would like more information on a particular college or stream, feel free to ask!','2025-11-21 01:50:35'),(16,NULL,'hello tell me about top colleges in manglore','Namaste! I\'d be happy to help you with your query.\n\nMangalore has a few excellent colleges, but I\'m assuming you\'re asking about top colleges in the country that have a presence in Mangalore. Unfortunately, I-ITs are not located in Mangalore.\n\nHowever, some of the top colleges in Mangalore are:\n\n1. National Institute of Technology Karnataka (NITK), Surathkal: A top engineering college in India, located about 20 km from Mangalore city.\n2. Manipal Academy of Higher Education (MAHE): A private university with a wide range of courses, including engineering, medicine, and more.\n3. Mangalore University: A state university offering various undergraduate and postgraduate courses.\n4. St. Aloysius College: A private college affiliated with Mangalore University, offering undergraduate and postgraduate courses.\n\nTo get more information about these colleges and others in Mangalore, I recommend checking their official websites, contacting them directly, or visiting websites like the National Institutional Ranking Framework (NIRF) for rankings and other details.\n\nWould you like me to provide more information on any of these colleges or help with something else?','2025-11-21 02:00:31'),(17,NULL,'i want the coure details in srinivas institute of technology valachil','I\'m Admit Genie, here to help.\n\nHowever, I couldn\'t find any information about the \"Srinivas Institute of Technology, Valachil\" in my database. Could you please provide more context or details about this college, such as its location or website? This will help me assist you better.\n\nAlternatively, you can also try visiting the college\'s official website or contacting them directly to get the most up-to-date information about their courses, eligibility, and fees.\n\nIf you\'re looking for information about the courses offered by the Srinivas Institute of Technology, Valachil, I would suggest checking the following sources:\n\n1. College Website: You can visit the college\'s website to get information about their courses, eligibility, and fees.\n2. NIRF Website: The National Institutional Ranking Framework (NIRF) website provides information about various colleges in India, including their courses and eligibility criteria.\n3. MHRD Website: The Ministry of Human Resource Development (MHRD) website also provides information about various colleges in India, including their courses and eligibility criteria.\n\nPlease let me know if there\'s anything else I can help you with!','2025-11-21 02:01:02'),(18,NULL,'who are you','Namaste! I\'m Admit Genie, your friendly AI assistant for Indian college admissions. I\'m here to help you navigate the complexities of college admissions in India. I have access to a vast database of information, including college rankings, course details, admission processes, exam schedules, and scholarship opportunities.\n\nMy primary goal is to assist you in finding the right college that suits your interests, academic background, and career aspirations. Whether you\'re a student looking for information on engineering colleges, medical colleges, or arts and humanities institutions, I\'m here to provide you with accurate and helpful guidance.\n\nFeel free to ask me any questions, and I\'ll do my best to assist you. If I don\'t have specific information, I\'ll let you know and suggest ways to find it.','2025-11-21 02:01:33'),(19,NULL,'hey','Namaste! I\'m Admit Genie, your friendly AI assistant for Indian college admissions. How can I help you today? Are you looking for information on college admissions, course details, or maybe scholarship opportunities? Let me know, and I\'ll do my best to assist you!','2025-11-21 02:01:42'),(20,NULL,'what scholarship opportunities','Namaste! As Admit Genie, I\'d be happy to assist you with scholarship opportunities in India.\n\nThere are numerous scholarship schemes available for Indian students, and I\'ll provide you with some popular ones. Keep in mind that eligibility criteria, application deadlines, and award amounts may vary. Here are a few notable ones:\n\n1. **Scholarships for Meritorious Students**:\n	* National Merit Scholarship Scheme (NMSS)\n	* Kendriya Sainik Board (KSB) Scholarships\n	* AICTE Pragati Scholarship Scheme\n2. **Scholarships for Economically Weaker Sections (EWS)**:\n	* EWS Scholarship (Central Government)\n	* State Government EWS Scholarships (varies by state)\n3. **Scholarships for Specific Communities**:\n	* SC/ST/OBC Scholarships (Central/State Government)\n	* Minority Scholarships (Central/State Government)\n4. **External Scholarships**:\n	* Bill Gates Scholarship (for Indian students pursuing higher education abroad)\n	* Google India Scholarship\n	* Tata Scholarships (varies by category)\n\nTo explore more scholarship opportunities, I recommend:\n\n* Visiting the official websites of the National Scholarship Portal (NSP) and the All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE).\n* Checking the website of the University Grants Commission (UGC) for scholarship schemes specifically for undergraduate and postgraduate students.\n* Looking into scholarship opportunities offered by private companies, foundations, and trusts.\n\nRemember to research and verify the eligibility criteria, application deadlines, and award amounts for each scholarship before applying.\n\nWould you like me to guide you further on the application process or provide more information on a specific scholarship?','2025-11-21 02:01:59'),(21,NULL,'hey','Namaste! I\'m Admit Genie, your friendly college ad