olarships:**\n\n1. **Tata Scholarship**: The Tata Group offers scholarships to students from economically weaker sections to pursue higher education.\n2. **Birla Scholarship**: The Birla Group offers scholarships to students from SC/ST and economically weaker sections to pursue higher education.\n\n**College-specific Scholarships:**\n\n1. Check with your college administration or website to see if they offer any scholarships or financial aid to students.\n2. Some colleges, like the Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs), offer scholarships to students based on their academic performance.\n\n**Other Scholarships:**\n\n1. **Bank of Baroda Scholarship**: The Bank of Baroda offers scholarships to students pursuing higher education.\n2. **HDFC Scholarship**: The HDFC Group offers scholarships to students pursuing higher education.\n\n**Tips:**\n\n1. **Eligibility criteria**: Ensure you meet the eligibility criteria for the scholarship you\'re applying for.\n2. **Application deadlines**: Check the application deadlines and apply well in advance to avoid missing the opportunity.\n3. **Document requirements**: Ensure you have all the required documents, such as your Aadhaar card, bank account details, and academic certificates, before applying.\n4. **Apply online**: Most scholarships can be applied for online through the official website or the NSP portal.\n\n**Suggested Next Steps:**\n\n1. Visit the NSP website ([www.scholarships.gov.in](http://www.scholarships.gov.in)) to explore the available scholarships.\n2. Check with your college administration or website to see if they offer any scholarships or financial aid.\n3. Research private scholarships offered by organizations like the Tata Group, Birla Group, and Bank of Baroda.\n\nI hope this information helps you get started with applying for scholarships. If you have any specific questions or need further assistance, please feel free to ask!','2025-12-05 09:59:45'),(40,NULL,'Tell me about admission deadlines','Namaste! As